
[1]flexuous

   FLEX'UOUS, a. [L. flexuosus.]

   1. Winding; having turns or windings; as a flexuous rivulet.

   2. Bending; winding; wavering; not steady; as a flexuous flame.

   3. In botany, bending or bent; changing its direction in a curve, from
   joint to joint, from bud to bud, or from flower to flower.
